        "timestamp": "2018-02-01 17:39:26.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi, Did you find something that using powermockito would be covered by Sonar's Test Coverage? Here is my finding: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/27925401/powermockito-disables-sonar-branch-coverage",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "f91499430c67fb67d2635deb41bed680213fb241",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2815,
          "name": "Michal Kabaj",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "michal.kabaj@nokia.com",
          "username": "kabayashi"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-02-02 11:13:21.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Hi, Did you find something that using powermockito would be covered\n > by Sonar's Test Coverage? Here is my finding: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/27925401/powermockito-disables-sonar-branch-coverage\n\nHello Takamune, No I did not search for this. I find using powermock or powermockito technical debt that enforces bad design and basically should be removed. Its better to rewrite the tests + refactor the code than to have empty coverage. Lack of coverage due to powermockito usage can actually be a good motivator for its removal:) \nAs part of the merge request I only \"restored\" the dependencies required by existing junits that use those libraries and but are not transitive. In the end they should be removed and the junits rewritten.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
